-- Defending Champion Chiefs to Host Brumbies in Super Rugby Final
-- B y   D a n   B a y n e s
-- 2013-07-27T17:53:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-27/defending-champion-chiefs-to-host-brumbies-in-super-rugby-final.html
The Chiefs will host the ACT
Brumbies in next week’s Super Rugby final as they seek to secure
back-to-back southern hemisphere provincial championships.  The Chiefs, who won their first title last year, beat the
record seven-time champion Crusaders 20-19 at Waikato Stadium in
Hamilton,  New Zealand , which will also be the site of the Aug. 3
final.  Australia ’s Brumbies defeated the Bulls 26-23 in
 Pretoria ,  South Africa , in today’s other semifinal.  Teams from New Zealand have won 11 of the previous 17
titles. The Chiefs and the Bulls had secured byes in the first
week of the playoffs and home semifinal advantage by finishing
the 15-team regular season in first and second place.  The Chiefs scored 17 straight points early in the second
half to erase a 9-3 deficit. Aaron Cruden scored a try and
kicked 10 points in the victory, while Lelia Masaga also touched
down.  Tevita Kiridrani’s try in the 78th minute gave the Brumbies
the away win. Jesse Moog also touched down for the Brumbies, who
will play for their third title, and Christian Lealiifano kicked
16 points. Morne Steyn booted six penalties for the Bulls and JJ
Engelbrecht touched down once.  To contact the reporter on this story:
